qas.question: What is the number of personnel in the army?
With what is the infantry brigade mainly equipped with?
What is the mechanized brigade mainly equipped with?

answers.text: Leopard 2 A6 tanks and M113 APC

qas.question: What does the Rapid Reaction Brigade consist of?
How many personnel does the Navy have?

context: The Army (<a0_0>21,000<a0_0/> personnel) comprises three brigades and other small units. An infantry brigade (mainly equipped with <a1_0>Pandur II APC<a1_0/>), a mechanized brigade (mainly equipped with <a2_0>Leopard 2 A6 tanks and M113 APC<a2_0/>) and a Rapid Reaction Brigade (consisting of <a3_0>paratroopers, commandos and rangers<a3_0/>). The Navy (<a4_0>10,700<a4_0/> personnel, of which 1,580 are marines) has five frigates, seven corvettes, two submarines, and 28 patrol and auxiliary vessels. The Air Force (7,500 personnel) has the Lockheed F-16 Fighting Falcon and the Dassault/Dornier Alpha Jet as the main combat aircraft.
